thread.title: Tesla tops 11,000 vehicles delivered

title: Tesla tops 11,000 vehicles delivered
text:
Sat, Jul 4, 2015, 7:13 AM NZST - New Zealand Markets closed Tesla tops 11,000 vehicles delivered AAP – 6 hours ago 

Tesla's second-quarter deliveries have surged 52 per cent to set a company record exceeding 11,000 vehicles. 
The Palo Alto, California, electric car maker surpassed 10,000 vehicles for the first time in the first three months of 2015 and on Thursday said it had broken that record, delivering 11,507 vehicles. 
Tesla makes only one car, the Model S sedan, but chief executive Elon Musk in June said he expects to begin deliveries of an SUV, the Model X, in three or four months. 
But, Tesla cautioned that record deliveries are not an indicator of overall financial results. The company has consistently lost money as it ramps up production. Despite record sales in the first quarter, the company lost $US154 million ($A201.68 million). @YahooNZBusiness on Twitter, become a fan on Facebook AAP
